  <discussion>The taxonomic and nomenclatural treatment of Sanguisorba stipulata has varied. Plants from northwest North America and northeast Asia are not taxonomically distinguishable, a conclusion reached also by Li C. L. et al. (1994). The name S. sitchensis has been customarily applied to North American plants; the oldest name available for a taxon bridging the Bering Strait is S. stipulata. An additional taxonomic question is the relationship of this taxon to eastern North American S. canadensis. While similar and undoubtedly closely related, the two differ in several morphologic characteristics, are strongly allopatric in distribution, and are here regarded as sibling species.</discussion>
